{"key":"post-12641100","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12641100</id>\n<content>You'd be better off shining the light in the sides.&amp;nbsp; More light will hit the substrate that way.&amp;nbsp; 80% of the surface area to absorb light is on the sides, only 20% is on the top.&amp;nbsp; Best bet would be to position the light slightly above and to one side of the tub.&amp;nbsp; Hopefully it's a clear tub with just a colored lid that you cut out?&amp;nbsp; If not, get one for next time.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12642046</next>\n<prev>12640527</prev>\n<first>12625193</first>\n<last>12642046</last>\n<when>1275012163</when>\n<utime>05/28/10 05:02 AM</utime>\n</post>"}